I have a bundle that provides an extension for the org.eclipse.core.runtime.adapters extension point.  No other classes (other than the IAdapterFactory implementation class) are accessed from outside this bundle, so the bundle is not loaded until the point when the adapter manager attempts to load the implementation class and then call the IAdapterFactory.getAdapter(Object,Class).  But the AdapterManager tests for the bundle being in active state (and this test fails) and incorrectly returns null.

Here's the AdapterManager.getAdapter(Object,Class) method (in 3.2):

	public Object getAdapter(Object adaptable, Class adapterType) {
		IAdapterFactory factory = (IAdapterFactory) getFactories(adaptable.getClass()).get(adapterType.getName());
		Object result = null;
		if (factory != null)
			result = factory.getAdapter(adaptable, adapterType);
		if (result == null && adapterType.isInstance(adaptable))
			return adaptable;
		return result;
	}

The 'factory' value is of type AdapterFactoryProxy, and so when the factory.getAdapter(adaptable,adapterType) method is called, the following method is invoked:

	public Object getAdapter(Object adaptableObject, Class adapterType) {
		if (!factoryLoaded)
			loadFactory(false);
		return factory == null ? null : factory.getAdapter(adaptableObject, adapterType);
	}

When the 'loadFactory(false)' method is called the following code is invoked:

	public IAdapterFactory loadFactory(boolean force) {
		synchronized (this) {
			if (factory != null || factoryLoaded)
				return factory;
			String bundleId = element.getContributor().getName();
			if (!force && Platform.getBundle(bundleId).getState() != Bundle.ACTIVE)
				return null;
			//set to true to prevent repeated attempts to load a broken factory
			factoryLoaded = true;
		}
                ...
	}

For my bundle (which has had no previous accesses to classes in the bundle, and therefore the bundle is not previously loaded) the test:

if (!force && Platform.getBundle(bundleId).getState() != Bundle.ACTIVE)
				return null;

fails and returns null rather than actually loading the bundle.  So the AdapterManager returns null rather than loading the bundle, then loading the IAdapterFactory implementation class, and calling its 
IAdapterManager.getAdapter(Class,Object) method.
